title: Sather Named New Superior Softball Coach
text:
Sather Named New Superior Softball Coach 
By Zach Schneider Sather Named New Superior Softball Coach October 8, 2015 Updated Oct 8, 2015 at 8:42 PM CDT 
Superior, WI (NNCNOW.com) --- Superior has named Mike Sather its new head softball coach ahead of the 2016 season, the school announced on Thursday afternoon. 
Sather spent 11 seasons as the Spartans head coach in the late 1980s and early 1990s, leading the program to the state tournament in the 1993 season. 
He replaces Amy Zembo, who resigned over the summer after spending 14 years in charge the program. 
Sather had spent the past two seasons as an assistant softball coach for Proctor.
